Dorsum – Prodorsum with four pairs of setae ( Figure 1A ); median propodosomal lobes weakly developed with fused base (variations in propodosomal lobes due to mounting are presented in Figure 2 A-C); outer propodosomal lobes reduced to small tubercles; setae v 2 about twice as long as setae v 1 ( Figure 2 ). Distance between members of first ( v 1 ) and second v ( 2 ) pair of propodosomal setae insertions 10 (8–12) and 47 (45–50), respectively. Dorsal body setae short, spatulate and serrate, 12–17 width, subequal in length except for v 1 far smaller, inserted on small tubercles ( Figure 1B ). Measurements of dorsal setae: v 1 11 (10–11); v 2 23 (22–26); sc 1 21 (21–25); sc 2 23 (21–25); c 1 25 (23–29); c 2 23 (21–26); c 3 23 (21–25); d 1 23 (21–25); d 2 23 (21–25); d 3 23 (21–23);
