Gnathosoma – Stylophore slightly notched anteriorly, longer than wide, as in female. Tibial claw of palpus bidentate. Palptarsus as in female with solenidion shorter than eupathidia (
Figure 8B
). Peritreme ends in small bulb with four pointed denticles at its distal margin (
Figure 8C
).

Aeadeagus – Without knob, bent dorsad near at right angle, weakly sigmoid, with tapering distal part and acute tip pointing caudad, shaft dorsal margin curved (
Figure 8D
).
